. I think he's name is Ryhask, something like that, He will ask if you want to learn about some orb, tell he &quot;I wish to learn&quot;. He will give you a coin, Now here is the important part, BIND right next to him, then port to west commons to find his friend Jahsohn Ak'Sot, He wanders around the zone wall going toward Kithicor. Give him the coin. Then GATE back to the lake. Now look at your exp. =) If you are a low lvl (ie 19) you will get a whole bubble of BLUE filled, 5 blue=1Yellow<br>I would not recommend doing this for the whole lvl, but getting past that first or last bubble makes it soooo much nicer. Verant will soon think this is not right and will nerf it so if you want try it, do so now. By the way, I went from the last two bubbles of 33 into 34 with this quest in about 2 1/2 hours.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwulfborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulfborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333399>(1/4/01 2:40:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5402.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: that last bubble =)</span><hr size=1> Friend of mine was doing the muffin quest in freeport when I wandered by with my newbie monk, then only level 3. He gave me a stack a muffins which I turned in. one stack of muffins gave me a blue bubble of xp. Went and bought myself a few more stacks and bought my way to 4th. (Incredibly boring but it cost less than a plat to do) 8) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utevarintreetamer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tevarin Treetamer</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333399>(1/6/01 12:27:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5402.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Excellent</span><hr size=1> I just want to verify that this is an EXCELLENT quest for exp. At hell level 30 it was taking me a few hours to get a blue bub of exp. Doing this I was able to get the last 2 orange bubbles in about 4 hours. I did have some trouble finding the mage guy. There are two wizzies by the single spawn in LR. Ignore these and head to the loc 1000, 1000. You will see an island with two aviaks on it. I'm not sure which direction, but if you are standing facing the aviak tower go to your left. If you have tracking, use it and look for the mage called Rykas. If not, just look for an island. Watch out for the goblin net master tho, he took me down once. Just ask Rykas &quot;i want to learn the tale&quot; i suggest making a hotkey. he will give you the coin and the rest is can be found in the first post. I agree with the first poster, this will probably be nerfed soon but i'm sure gonna try to get the mostl out of it i can. I suggest you do the same.<br><br>Hipokrit Procrastinator<br>31 druid of lanys <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udolgeruk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dolgeruk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333399>(1/9/01 2:30:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5402.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: that last bubble =)</span><hr size=1> Here is the lock of Rykas, the mage in LOIO:<br><br>959 -643<br><br><